  "prompt": "What are div1 and div2 on topcoder?",
  "response": "On Topcoder, Div1 and Div2 are divisions used to categorize competitors based on their skill level in competitive programming contests.\n\n1. **Division 1 (Div1):**\n   - This is the higher division for more experienced and skilled competitors.\n   - Typically, it includes competitors with higher ratings, usually above 1200.\n   - The problems in Div1 are more difficult and challenging compared to Div2.\n   \n2. **Division 2 (Div2):**\n   - This is the lower division for less experienced competitors or those developing their skills.\n   - It includes competitors with ratings below 1200.\n   - The problems in Div2 are relatively easier compared to those in Div1.\n\nWhen a contest is organized, participants are divided into these divisions based on their current rating, ensuring that they compete with others of similar skill levels. This system helps maintain a fair competitive environment and provides suitable challenges for everyone involved.",
